{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "We model the word-swapping operator as a weight matrix whose weights are calculated as negative gradients with respect to the token mask (Ebrahimi et al., 2017; Guo et al., 2021).",
    "When updating an adversarial suffix at t-th iteration, we learn 256 candidates with hotflip (Ebrahimi et al., 2017; Zou et al., 2023).",
    "Every candidate differs from the current adversarial suffix with one token.",
    "We forward all those candidates to victim LLM and evaluate their loss values.",
    "The candidate with the minimum loss is selected as the adversarial suffix at the (t + 1)-th iteration."
  ],
